\section{Directory layout (Hive partitioning)}{


\code{dhs_read()} expects \code{path} to be the root of a directory tree partitioned
in this order, with one parquet file per survey at the leaf:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{path/
  file_type=GE/
    country_code=TG/
      survey_year=2017/
        survey_id=TGGE8I/
          data.parquet
  file_type=KR/
    country_code=TG/
      survey_year=2017/
        survey_id=TGKR81/
          data.parquet
  file_type=PR/...
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

Partition keys are read literally as \code{file_type=...}, \code{country_code=...},
\code{survey_year=...}, \code{survey_id=...}. Allowed \code{file_type} values are
\code{PR}, \code{HR}, \code{IR}, \code{KR}, \code{GE}, \code{BR}, \code{MR}, \code{WI}. \code{country_code} is the
DHS two-letter code (e.g. \code{TG}, \code{BU}, \code{KE}).
